snippet.textDisplay:
In Sweden with a license plate you can get the following for free online:
History of where the car has been sold before on numerous different sites like "Swedish craigslist" etc and at what price it was listed at.
Car inspection protocols (we have to get our cars inspected every 14 months).
If the car has any unpaid taxes or parking tickets.
SSN of all current and past owners of the vechicle, crime records of all owners, addresses, income, credit history, insurance info, social media accounts. The list goes on and on.
Back in the day you could get more or less all this info straight from our DMV. But nowadays you if want the complete info you just gotta know which websites to look and search at to get the info you want.

Damn even with just a first and last name you can get all this info.

snippet.textDisplay:
If you think those traffic cameras are just for generating Revenue you are mistaken. Big brother is watching.

There is a new app out that gives law enforcement complete personal information of a person based on a picture In just a few seconds. Many cold cases are being solved with it. Peter Theil and this brilliant coder guy put it together. It uses billions and billions of pictures scraped from the internet to somehow ID you accurately and quickly from a picture taken by phone, cctv, traffic cam...whatever.

Imagine the implications in the general Public's hands. A person could just take your picture in a bar and find out everything about you. Immediately. A pedophile could take a picture of you at the park and find out where you live.

This is a technology that both Facebook and Google refused to pursue based on those implications(imagine that) and now a couple of yahoos who just want to make a buck have done it....and all law enforcement has access to it.

Except New Jersey. They've banned it's use by law enforcement in New Jersey. But that doesn't mean they don't use it to find out who they're dealing with and then go from there.

Some computer somewhere is probably noting my comments about this issue right now and putting it in my file.
